  "prompt": "What countries can I travel to without an Indian passport?",
  "response": "As an Indian passport holder, you can travel to several countries, but most will require a visa either on arrival or via an e-Visa. However, there are a few countries and territories where Indian passport holders can travel without a visa for short stays. Here\u2019s a list of countries you can typically visit without a prior visa:\n\n1. **Nepal**\n2. **Bhutan**\n3. **Maldives** (visa on arrival for 30 days)\n4. **Mauritius** (visa on arrival for 90 days)\n5. **Fiji** (visa on arrival for 4 months)\n6. **Dominica** (visa-free for 21 days)\n7. **Grenada** (visa-free for 30 days)\n8. **Saint Kitts and Nevis** (visa-free for 90 days)\n9. **Saint Vincent and the Grenadines** (visa-free for 30 days)\n10. **Jamaica** (visa-free for 90 days)\n11. **Haiti** (visa-free for 90 days)\n12. **Barbados** (visa-free for 90 days)\n13. **El Salvador** (visa-free for 90 days)\n\nPlease note that visa policies may change, and specific entry requirements like health or security regulations may apply, so it's advisable to check with the official consulate or embassy of the country you plan to visit for the most current information before making travel plans.",
